 Given my cautious nature, I would lean towards choosing a strategy that provides some level of security and predictability. In this game, if we both consistently choose the same option, we can earn 45$ per round when we both pick R and 20$ per round when we both pick B.

However, there's a significant risk in picking R every time because if my opponent picks B, I will receive nothing for that round. On the other hand, if I pick B while they pick R, they get 40$ and I only get 20$. This means that over the course of 75 rounds, I could potentially miss out on 30$ per round by choosing R consistently.

In contrast, picking B every time would mean that I will always earn at least 20$ per round. While I won't have the potential to gain an extra 25$ in each R-R round, I also won't lose anything in R-B rounds either. Therefore, considering my risk aversion and preference for predictability, I would likely choose B as my strategy. {B}
